item.title: Street Fighter: Legacy - Short Fan Film
item.description:
Street Fighter: Legacy - Short Fan Film
*FOR BEST VIEWING EXPERIENCE, WATCH IN HD AND WITH GOOD SPEAKERS OR HEADPHONES.* 'Street Fighter-Legacy' a Streetlight Films production, co-directed by Joey Ansah and Owen Trevor, produced by Jacqueline Quella and stars Jon Foo as Ryu and Christian Howard as Ken. 'StreetFighter-Legacy' a liveaction short film fan project, based on the popular Capcom gaming franchise: Street Fighter. Officially endorsed by Capcom StreetFighter Legacy has been a labour of love and passion project for its creator, Joey Ansah, who not only conceived and pitched the project, but also co-directed, co-wrote and choreographed it, alongside cameo'ing in the film. Collaborating, creative partner and long time friend Christian Howard was part of the project from day one, co-writing the script and story elements, as well as further down the line, storyboarding the film, being assistant fight choreographer and most importantly playing Ken Masters. Streetlight repped Australian Director Owen Trevor came onboard to co-direct the film. His experience and style carried forward from shooting on 3 series of the acclaimed 'Top Gear' have really been an asset to the project and given it a strong visual flair. Promotional Photography by Theo Chalmers : www.theochalmers.com Related Websites: www.joeyansah.com www.lankyboy.com www.streetlightfilms.co.uk www.christianhoward.co.uk www.jonfoo.co.uk www.nigelalbermaniche.co.uk http://www.myspace.com/theechorebellion (patrick Gill composer)

item.title: Talking Mickey at Disneyland
item.description:
Talking Mickey at Disneyland
Recorded on May 3, 2010 using a Flip Video camcorder. Notes: In response to all those who are interested: this was a video taken at Mickeys House in Toontown on Monday May 3rd, 2010 around 1pm. My wife, Father, Sister (Margaret in video), and Daughter (Maddie in video) waited to meet Mickey thinking that it was the traditional meet and greet that we experienced a year and a half ago much to our surprise they ushered us into a room where Mickey interacted with our group of 15 people or so. I should note that before entering the room we signed a form acknowledging it was alright for Disney to film the session for internal purposes (or something to that extent). I do not know if we were part of a test group or if everyone that day experienced the same interaction with Mickey. I can say it was a truly amazing experience.

item.title: Machete illegal trailer
item.description:
Machete illegal trailer
Machete è un film del 2010 diretto da Robert Rodriguez, interpretato da Danny Trejo e Robert De Niro. L'uscita è prevista il 3 settembre 2010. Questo film è l'espansione del fake trailer di Grindhouse (2007) diretto dallo stesso Rodriguez. Inoltre lo stesso personaggio lo troviamo sempre in un altro film di Rodriquez, ovvero Spy Kids (2001), sempre interpretato da Danny Trejo con Antonio Banderas alias Gregorio Cortez, fratello di Machete. http://www.moviesushi.it/html/news-Ecco_il_trailer_illegale_di_Machete-5567.html Machete is an upcoming action film, directed by Robert Rodriguez and Ethan Maniquis. The film will star Danny Trejo in his first lead role as the title character. The film also stars Michelle Rodriguez, Cheech Marin, Lindsay Lohan, Don Johnson, Jessica Alba, Steven Seagal, Robert DeNiro, Jeff Fahey, and Cheryl Chin. The film is an expansion of a fake trailer Rodriguez directed for the 2007 film Grindhouse and centers around the character of Machete Cortez, who previously appeared as the uncle of the protagonists in the Spy Kids films. Filmed in autumn 2009, the film will be released in the United States on September 3, 2010 by 20th Century Fox
